  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to weston</title>

    <para>
      <application>weston</application> is the reference implementation of a Wayland compositor.
      Weston creates its unix socket file (for example, wayland-0) in the directory 
      specified by the required environment variable $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR. 
      Clients use the same variable to find that socket. This is provided using systemd.
    </para>

    &lfs75_checked;

